{"_attachments":{},"_id":"testcafe-reporter-minimal","_rev":"293843-61f1c8c3cdb16e9889f3b244","author":{"name":"Developer Express Inc.","url":"https://devexpress.com"},"description":"Minimal TestCafe reporter plugin.","dist-tags":{"latest":"2.2.0"},"license":"MIT","maintainers":[{"name":"kirovboris","email":"boris.s.kirov@gmail.com"},{"name":"romanresh","email":"romanresh@live.com"}],"name":"testcafe-reporter-minimal","readme":"# testcafe-reporter-minimal\n[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/DevExpress/testcafe-reporter-minimal.svg)](https://travis-ci.org/DevExpress/testcafe-reporter-minimal)\n\nThis is the **Minimal** reporter plugin for [TestCafe](http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe).\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"https://raw.github.com/DevExpress/testcafe-reporter-minimal/master/media/preview.png\" alt=\"preview\" />\n</p>\n\n## Install\n\nThis reporter is shipped with TestCafe by default. In most cases, you won't need to install it separately.\n\nHowever, if you need to install this reporter, you can use the following command.\n\n```\nnpm install testcafe-reporter-minimal\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nWhen you run tests from the command line, specify the reporter name by using the `--reporter` option:\n\n```\ntestcafe chrome 'path/to/test/file.js' --reporter minimal\n```\n\n\nWhen you use API, pass the reporter name to the `reporter()` method:\n\n```js\ntestCafe\n    .createRunner()\n    .src('path/to/test/file.js')\n    .browsers('chrome')\n    .reporter('minimal') // <-\n    .run();\n```\n\n## Author\nDeveloper Express Inc. (https://devexpress.com)\n","time":{"created":"2022-01-26T22:18:43.406Z","modified":"2025-12-03T13:14:22.708Z","2.1.0":"2017-01-02T21:08:41.150Z","2.0.0":"2016-07-27T11:52:59.999Z","1.0.2":"2016-06-29T14:06:55.879Z","1.0.1":"2016-03-24T12:05:23.019Z","1.0.0":"2015-12-09T11:01:58.271Z","2.2.0":"2023-05-03T07:18:05.662Z"},"versions":{"2.1.0":{"name":"testcafe-reporter-minimal","version":"2.1.0","description":"Minimal TestCafe reporter plu